         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>ARCHER HPC Facility — Computational Science and Engineering (CSE)</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>PR120040</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="72230000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The ARCHER service comprises the hardware Computational Science and Engineering (CSE) support, Service Provision (SP) support, hardware accommodation support and external users UKRI, as managing agent for the national HPC facility is extending (a period of up to 15 months) the existing CSE contract for ARCHER which includes:</P>
               <P>— integration with technology (in conjunction with the hardware and service providers),</P>
               <P>— supporting the user community in developing and optimising the scientific codes that are run on ARCHER,</P>
               <P>— resolving user code problems,</P>
               <P>— providing comprehensive technical training for users across Tier 1 and integrating with the EPSRC Tier 2 HPC layer.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_RANGE_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">
               <LOW>2400000</LOW>
               <HIGH>2630000</HIGH>
            </VAL_RANGE_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72260000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72212000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="72212980"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Throughout UK.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>UKRI, as managing agent for the national HPC facility is extending the existing 5 year contract by a period of up to 15 months to ensure continuity of the existing ARCHER facility until plans for a replacement ARCHER2 have been agreed, approved and procured.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>Due to delays in the procurement of a replacement facility (ARCHER2) the existing ARCHER facility is being extended until such time that plans for ARCHER2 are agreed, approved and a replacement facility procured. The Computational Science and Engineering (CSE) element of the ARCHER facility cannot be separated from the hardware and associated services without serious disruption to the ARCHER service and significant additional cost were CSE and SP services not to extend in line with the hardware, the ARCHER service would not be able to function. The loss of the compute capability would affect over 6 500 regular users of the ARCHER Service and the disruption of over 800 research projects currently dependent on the computing power of the ARCHER machine.</P>
                     <P>Any new CSE provider cannot be sourced currently as the nature of the CSE service is such that a change in provider on the same technology platform would cause significant disruption to the ARCHER service.</P>
                     <P>In addition, agreement and approval of plans for ARCHER2 would not be able to be procured by the end of the existing contract.</P>
                     <P>The extension to this contract is being made under Regulation 72 (1) (b) of the Public Contract Regulations 2015.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
